# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generic all-purpose .gitignore
# Stack: C# / .NET · TypeScript · Vue · Tailwind · Node (Vite)
# IDEs:  Visual Studio · JetBrains (Rider / WebStorm) · VS Code
#
# Canonical copy lives in dotfiles/git/gitignore.
# Drop into a project with:  cp ~/dotfiles/git/gitignore ./.gitignore
# Reconciled against the github/gitignore templates (VisualStudio,
# JetBrains, VisualStudioCode, Node, macOS, Windows) for this stack.
# Lockfiles (package-lock.json, pnpm-lock.yaml, yarn.lock) stay COMMITTED.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── Secrets & environment ─────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.*
*.env
!.env.example
*.local

# Private keys, certificates, credentials
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.credentials.json
.credentials.json
credentials.json
*-credentials.json
service-account*.json
.npmrc.local

# JetBrains HTTP client — private env (tokens / secrets)
http-client.private.env.json

# ASP.NET app settings — appsettings*.json holds real data, so ignore it.
# Commit a secret-free sample instead (e.g. appsettings.sample.json).
appsettings*.json
!appsettings.[Ss]ample.json
!appsettings.[Ee]xample.json


